  "text": "The HotSpot JIT compilation pipeline is defined across five key C++ header files in OpenJDK's src/hotspot/share/ directory:\n\n1. **CompileBroker** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compileBroker.hpp:165): The central broker that manages all compilation requests, maintains compile queues, and coordinates the assignment of compilation tasks to compiler threads. It is defined as an AllStatic class and oversees the entire compilation infrastructure.\n\n2. **CompilerThread** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/compilerThread.hpp:60): A specialized thread type that extends JavaThread and executes compilation tasks. Each CompilerThread runs a specific compiler instance and processes compilation jobs from the compile queue.\n\n3. **Compiler (C1)** (src/hotspot/share/c1/c1_Compiler.hpp:34): The first-tier JIT compiler implementation that extends AbstractCompiler. It provides fast compilation with basic optimizations, suitable for code that doesn't meet thresholds for deeper optimization.\n\n4. **C2Compiler** (src/hotspot/share/opto/c2compiler.hpp:36): The second-tier optimizing JIT compiler that extends AbstractCompiler. It performs aggressive optimizations including escape analysis, loop unrolling, and inlining for code paths that are frequently executed.\n\n5. **AbstractCompiler** (src/hotspot/share/compiler/abstractCompiler.hpp:73): The abstract base class for all JIT compiler implementations (C1 and C2), defining the common interface and managing compiler state, statistics, and initialization. It provides the framework that both tier compilers inherit from.\n\nThis architecture implements a two-tier compilation strategy where CompileBroker coordinates compilation work, CompilerThread instances execute the work, and AbstractCompiler provides the base implementation for both C1 (fast, lower optimization) and C2 (slow, higher optimization) tiers."
}

